Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.21,0:01:40.16,HnF,,0,0,0,,Koyomi Tea
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.78,0:01:43.09,HnF,,0,0,0,,Octubre
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.28,0:01:51.96,HnF,,0,0,0,,Hermano, ¿tú crees en los fantasmas y esas cosas?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.16,0:01:53.66,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿En los fantasmas?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.60,0:01:55.38,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿Por qué lo dices?{What’s with that.}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.38,0:01:57.14,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿Te dijo algo Sengoku?{Did you hear something from Sengoku?}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.18,0:02:01.89,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿Qué tiene que ver Nadeko en esto?{Why is Nadeko-chan’s name coming up?}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.89,0:02:04.93,HnF,,0,0,0,,A veces dices cosas que no tienen sentido.{Onii-chan, sometimes you say things that make no sense.}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.93,0:02:06.26,HnF,,0,0,0,,No, no era nada.{No, it's nothing!}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.05,0:02:09.44,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿Pero por qué has preguntado eso de repente?{But why are you suddenly asking about ghosts?}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.44,0:02:12.97,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿Puede ser que un fantasma apareciera en tu club de ceremonia del té?{What, is it something like a ghost appearing in your tea ceremony club?}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.97,0:02:14.36,HnF,,0,0,0,,¡Exacto!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.36,0:02:15.41,HnF,,0,0,0,,¡Qué rápido te has dado cuenta!{¡Me has sorprendido con eso!}{I’m surprised you figured it out}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.17,0:02:16.22,HnF,,0,0,0,,Parece que la suerte me sonríe.{Una deducción aleatoria afortunada.}{A lucky random guess.}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.50,0:02:21.90,HnF,,0,0,0,,Sí, realmente un fantasma {\i1}apareció{\i0} en el club.{Or rather, it’s more correct to say a ghost appeared in the tea ceremony club}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.31,0:02:25.41,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿Qué quieres decir con que realmente apareció?{What do you mean by it appeared?}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.41,0:02:28.72,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿Qué tipo de rastros dejó en el club?{Were there traces of it left in the club room?}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.02,0:02:33.68,HnF,,0,0,0,,No, no dejó nada realmente...{No, I wouldn’t say it left any traces…}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.68,0:02:37.17,HnF,,0,0,0,,No hay rastros de que ese niño estuviese ahí.{There’s no objective evidence that that kid was there.}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.49,0:02:38.24,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,¿Ese niño?{That kid?}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.24,0:02:39.48,HnF,,0,0,0,,Es una manera extraña de referirse a eso.{That’s a strangely specific way of referring to it.}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.86,0:02:41.93,HnF,,0,0,0,,Tsukihi, voy a decirte algo que te ayudará.{Tsukihi, I’ll tell you about something good.}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.93,0:02:46.15,HnF,,0,0,0,,Si no hay rastros, significa que\N ¡no hay ningún fantasma!{If there’s no evidence, that means there was no ghost!}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.15,0:02:48.15,HnF,,0,0,0,,Y con esto se resuelve el asunto.{Yup, that settles the matter.}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.54,0:02:51.52,HnF,,0,0,0,,Ya podemos hablar sobre otras cosas.{We can just chat about something else now.}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.62,0:03:01.20,HnF,,0,0,0,,¡Lo digo en serio,\N esto no es ninguna tontería!{I want this to be a proper consultation! Not some idle chatter!}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.47,0:03:02.82,HnF,,0,0,0,,Vale, entendido.{Okay, okay.}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.82,0:03:04.03,HnF,,0,0,0,,Por poco.{Whoa there, Nelly.}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.03,0:03:06.21,HnF,,0,0,0,,Lo entiendo, pero saca ese bolígrafo de aquí.{I get it, so put that ballpoint pen away.}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.21,0:03:07.25,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿Que lo saque?{Put it away?}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.25,0:03:10.56,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿Qué color exactamente de estos tres quieres que saque?{Which of the three colors in this tricolor pen are you telling me to put away?}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.56,0:03:11.54,HnF,,0,0,0,,Todos.{All of them!}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.54,0:03:13.17,HnF,,0,0,0,,Rojo, azul, negro, todos ellos.{Red, blue, black, all of them!}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.17,0:03:15.21,HnF,,0,0,0,,Entonces, ¿de qué querías hablar antes?{So, what exactly are you saying here?}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.21,0:03:18.89,HnF,,0,0,0,,Si no hay ningún rastro del fantasma que dices que apareció en el club.{There’s no evidence for the ghost that you say appeared in the tea ceremony club?}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.27,0:03:21.86,HnF,,0,0,0,,Eso dije, ¿es que no me estás escuchando?{That’s what I said! Weren’t you listening?}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.86,0:03:26.45,HnF,,0,0,0,,Entonces, ¿has sido tú la que ha demostrado que no había ningún fantasma?{If I were to guess, would you be the one that proved that there was no ghost?}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.70,0:03:28.64,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿Como lo has sabido?{Wow. How’d you figure that out?}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.32,0:03:32.15,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,Imagino que los sucesos han sido algo así:{The story probably went something like this:}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.15,0:03:35.82,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,Se extendieron rumores sobre un fantasma que aparece en el club.{There were rumors being spread about a ghost appearing in the tea ceremony club room,}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.82,0:03:41.07,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,Tsukihi, en solitario, no como parte de las {\i1}Fire Sisters{\i0},{Tsukihi, most likely not as part of the Fire Sisters but as Araragi Tsukihi individually,}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.07,0:03:44.94,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,se puso a investigarlo, y lo resolvió.{Set out to investigate that rumor. And she resolved it.}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.49,0:03:47.97,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿Qué crees que debería hacer?{What do you think I should do, onii-chan?}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.97,0:03:48.97,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿Eh? ¿Sobre qué?{Huh? About what?}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.30,0:03:56.92,HnF,,0,0,0,,Fui capaz de explicar lógicamente que no había ningún fantasma,{I was able to logically explain the fact that there was no ghost…}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.92,0:04:00.02,HnF,,0,0,0,,pero nadie me creyó.{But nobody believes it.}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.45,0:04:03.56,HnF,,0,0,0,,Todos creen en el fantasma en vez de en mí.{Everyone believes in the ghost instead of believing in me.}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.96,0:04:09.10,HnF,,0,0,0,,Me llevé todas las pruebas circunstanciales,{I took all the circumstantial evidence,}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.10,0:04:13.89,HnF,,0,0,0,,incluyendo la declaración del testigo que inició el rumor sobre "la octava persona"{including the witness account that started the whole rumor about an 'eighth person’}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.89,0:04:16.57,HnF,,0,0,0,,a pesar de que el club solo tiene siete personas,{in the tea ceremony club despite it having only seven members,}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.57,0:04:18.77,HnF,,0,0,0,,a quienes combatí{refuté} lógicamente una por una.{and logically refuted them one by one.}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.77,0:04:20.44,HnF,,0,0,0,,Lógicamente.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.44,0:04:24.00,HnF,,0,0,0,,No es necesario que destaques lógicamente, te hace parecer mentirosa.{You don’t need to emphasize logically. It almost sounds like you’re lying.}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.00,0:04:25.66,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿Me estás llamando mentirosa? {Are you calling me a liar? How rude!}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.66,0:04:30.16,HnF,,0,0,0,,Después de todo lo que he tenido que pasar para probar la inexistencia de la octava persona.{So after going through quite a lot of trouble I managed to disprove the existence of the 'eighth person,’}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.16,0:04:32.50,HnF,,0,0,0,,Pero cuando se lo dije a los demás, respondieron:{but when I told everyone, they just said this:}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.50,0:04:35.17,HnF,,0,0,0,,'Puede que sea así, pero qué más da,{'That might be the case, but whatever}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.17,0:04:38.25,HnF,,0,0,0,,lo que dice Tsukihi puede ser cierto,{What Tsukihi-chan says might be right,}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.25,0:04:40.80,HnF,,0,0,0,,y puede ser esa la respuesta,{and that might be the case in theory,}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.80,0:04:44.18,HnF,,0,0,0,,pero aún así, la octava persona puede que siga existiendo'.{but, even so, the "eighth person” might still exist’}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.18,0:04:47.21,HnF,,0,0,0,,¡Eso dijeron!\N Así lo rumores no van a acabarse nunca.{is what they keep saying! The rumors just won’t stop!}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.50,0:04:53.14,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿Tú que opinas, hermano?{So what do you think, onii-chan?}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.14,0:04:54.93,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿Qué crees que debería hacer?{What do you think I should do?}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.93,0:04:56.29,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿Qué qué creo deberías hacer?{What you should do?}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.29,0:04:58.98,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿Qué crees que debería hacer en este momento?{What do you think I should do in this situation?}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.98,0:05:05.70,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿Cómo podría decírselo? Les dije lo que pasaba, y todo el mundo lo entendió,{How should I put it. I asserted what was right, and everyone understands that it was right,}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.70,0:05:11.08,HnF,,0,0,0,,los conflictos se terminaron ya, {so the confrontation, the conflict of opinion, is all over now,}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.08,0:05:15.58,HnF,,0,0,0,,pero los rumores siguen por ahí{expandiéndose}...{but the circumstances haven’t changed at all from before…}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.58,0:05:20.13,HnF,,0,0,0,,Como si lo que fuera 'cierto' no tuviera ningún efecto en ellos.{It’s as if what’s 'right’ has no meaning, and there’s no effect.}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.13,0:05:21.64,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿Qué debería hacer?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.64,0:05:24.02,HnF,,0,0,0,,Pasaron de ti sin ni siquiera discutir,{Without even arguing against it, they just ignored you}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.61,0:05:29.69,HnF,,0,0,0,,y continuaron hablando sobre esa 'octava persona' ¿cierto?{and continued to make a racket over this 'eighth person,’ is that right?}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.86,0:05:31.03,HnF,,0,0,0,,Eso es.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.50,0:05:35.56,HnF,,0,0,0,,En ese caso,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.56,0:05:36.69,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿qué consejo le podría dar?{what sort of advice could I give?}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.15,0:05:41.02,HnF,,0,0,0,,Oye Tsukihi, ¿qué quieres exactamente que haga yo?{Hey, Tsukihi-chan. So, what exactly do you want me to do?}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.22,0:05:43.69,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿A qué te refieres con eso?{What’s with that question?}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.69,0:05:46.81,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿No estabas escuchando lo que dije?{Onii-chan weren’t you listening to what I was saying?}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.81,0:05:48.94,HnF,,0,0,0,,No deberías sorprenderte tanto con eso...{Hey, you don’t need to look so surprised…}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.72,0:05:52.72,HnF,,0,0,0,,No deberías sorprenderte tanto con eso \Ncuando parece que vas a agredirme.{You don’t need to look so surprised while sounding like you’re going to attack me.}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.16,0:05:58.81,HnF,,0,0,0,,He estado muy cerca de ser teñido en tres colores.{My skin had come very close to being dyed in three colors.}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.34,0:06:01.00,HnF,,0,0,0,,Dímelo simplemente, Tsukihi.{Just give it to me straight, Tsukihi-chan.}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.00,0:06:03.57,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿Qué quieres que haga?{What do you want me to do?}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.57,0:06:06.34,HnF,,0,0,0,,Me molesta cuando dices eso,{It bothers me when you say it like that,}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.34,0:06:10.09,HnF,,0,0,0,,pero eso, quiero escuchar tu opinión.{but, so, like, I want to hear your opinion.}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.09,0:06:12.66,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿Crees en los fantasmas?{Onii-chan, do you believe in ghosts?}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.66,0:06:14.02,HnF,,0,0,0,,Ella volvió a su primera pregunta.{She returned to her very first question}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.88,0:06:19.02,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿Eh? ¿Por qué estás tardando tanto en responder?{What? Why do you look so cornered trying to answer, onii-chan?}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.02,0:06:21.95,HnF,,0,0,0,,Esto es algo que puedes responder con un simple 'sí' o 'no'.{This is just something you can answer and finish off with a simple 'yes’ or 'no’, you know?}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.95,0:06:23.27,HnF,,0,0,0,,No exactamente, Tsukihi.{No, no, Tsukihi-chan.}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.27,0:06:28.28,HnF,,0,0,0,,Los problemas mundiales no se acaban simplemente con 'sí' o 'no'.{The problems of the world aren't all easily finished off with a simple 'yes’ or 'no.’}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.28,0:06:29.45,HnF,,0,0,0,,Conque era eso.{Is that so?}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.45,0:06:33.48,HnF,,0,0,0,,En ese caso, a mí me vale con un simple 'sí' o 'no'.{In that case I’m okay with finishing off onii-chan with a simple 'yes’ or 'no.’}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.64,0:06:35.45,HnF,,0,0,0,,Entonces, 'no'.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.45,0:06:37.54,HnF,,0,0,0,,No creo en los fantasmas.{I don’t believe in ghosts.}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.54,0:06:41.13,HnF,,0,0,0,,Todos los miembros del club\N excepto tú, están equivocados.{All the tea ceremony club members besides you are definitely wrong,}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.13,0:06:45.21,HnF,,0,0,0,,Y puedo asegurar que estás en lo correcto,\N así que no te preocupes.{and I can guarantee that you’re correct, so don’t worry about it anymore.}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.21,0:06:49.22,HnF,,0,0,0,,Intenta creer en tu opinión hasta el final.{You just stay the way you are, and stay true to your own correctness.}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.42,0:06:51.22,HnF,,0,0,0,,Vale.{Ciertamente sí.}{You’re right.}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.22,0:06:53.68,HnF,,0,0,0,,Pero aún así me preocupa.{But it still bothers me.}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.02,0:06:59.35,HnF,,0,0,0,,Aceptase o no la existencia de la octava persona,{It’s not like her acceptance or denial the existence of the 'eighth person'}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.35,0:07:05.27,HnF,,0,0,0,,eso no iba a causar la dispersión del club o algún problema así.{will cause the tea ceremony club to break up, or anything serious like that.}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.27,0:07:07.71,HnF,,0,0,0,,Es solo que ella se siente impotente.{It's just that shes hitting a wall.}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.71,0:07:08.84,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿Impotente?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.84,0:07:13.14,HnF,,0,0,0,,Para alguien que defiende la justicia, estar en un lugar{As someone who advocates justice, being in an environment}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.14,0:07:15.83,HnF,,0,0,0,,donde ignoran lo que es 'correcto', le hace sentir molesta.{that ignores something that's right makes her feel ill at ease.}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.55,0:07:24.04,HnF,,0,0,0,,No escasean situaciones donde todo es irracional{en las que se impone lo irracional a lo real}.{Situations where the unreasonable or irrational are in control actually happen pretty often.}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.61,0:07:28.48,HnF,,0,0,0,,Aunque lidiar con eso puede ser muy útil en el futuro.{Experiencing irrationality like this can be useful for the future, right?}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.82,0:07:30.26,HnF,,0,0,0,,Irracional...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.26,0:07:33.00,HnF,,0,0,0,,Yo también creo que la verdad ha sido perseguida lo suficiente.{But I think reason has already been hunted down enough}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.44,0:07:36.75,HnF,,0,0,0,,Eso me hace querer apoyar a Tsukihi.{so personally it makes me want to become Tsukihi-chan’s ally.}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.75,0:07:40.24,HnF,,0,0,0,,A ti siempre te ha gustado ayudar a chicas adorables.{You’ve always been the ally of cute girls, though.}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.24,0:07:43.56,HnF,,0,0,0,,No, en este caso no tiene que ver con que sea adorable.{No, cuteness is not related in this case.}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.56,0:07:48.51,HnF,,0,0,0,,Si no, podría ser que los otros seis miembros del club sean aún más adorables.{Because if I said that, it’s possible that the other six members of the tea ceremony club might also be cute!}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.76,0:07:50.69,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿Cómo puede venir eso al caso?{What kind of an idea is that?}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.01,0:07:54.49,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿No te pasa a ti también{¿No es también tu caso}, Araragi?{But, aren’t you like that, too, Araragi-senpai?}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.49,0:07:58.29,HnF,,0,0,0,,Ambos conocemos las excentricidades.{Because you and I know about oddities,}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.86,0:08:03.33,HnF,,0,0,0,,Conocemos lo irracional, lo absurdo, lo ilógico.{because we know about the irrational, the unreasonable, the absurd.}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.06,0:08:08.50,HnF,,0,0,0,,Por eso quiero apoyar a Tsukihi.{That’s exactly why I want to become Tsukihi-chan’s ally.}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.50,0:08:13.24,HnF,,0,0,0,,Porque está luchando por negar la existencia de las excentricidades, por la realidad.{For Tsukihi-chan, who’s trying to deny oddities, who’s sacrificing herself for reality.}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.30,0:08:18.10,HnF,,0,0,0,,Si lo dices así, supongo que estaré de acuerdo.{When you say it like that, then I want to agree,}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.10,0:08:20.81,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿Pero eso no lo hace una lucha en vano?{but even so, it can’t be helped, can it?}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.81,0:08:22.53,HnF,,0,0,0,,No hay nada que podamos hacer.{There’s nothing we can do about it, is there?}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.97,0:08:25.65,HnF,,0,0,0,,Si insistes tanto, Araragi...{If you were to insist, Araragi-senpai,}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.65,0:08:30.06,HnF,,0,0,0,,¡Estoy dispuesta a entrar{irrumpir, penetrar?} en el club de ceremonia del té de la secundaria Tsuganoki!{then I wouldn't mind marching into Tsuganoki Second Junior High’s Tea Ceremony Club myself!}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.06,0:08:31.94,HnF,,0,0,0,,No insisto.{I won't insist.}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.94,0:08:35.62,HnF,,0,0,0,,Solo me preguntaba si hay alguna manera de satisfacer a Tsukihi.{Though I just wonder if there is any way to calm Tsukihi’s temper.}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.62,0:08:37.26,HnF,,0,0,0,,Sí que la hay.{That, we can do.}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.35,0:08:43.57,HnF,,0,0,0,,Si solo quieres aplacar a Tsukihi, existe una manera para eso.{If Araragi-senpai’s goal is just to placate Tsukihi-chan for now, then there is a way!}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.57,0:08:47.93,HnF,,0,0,0,,No me refería a aplacar exactamente, pero... ¿Cuál es esa manera?{It’s not exactly that I want to placate her… but there is?}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.93,0:08:51.55,HnF,,0,0,0,,Aunque eso tiene un problema.{Sin embargo, hay un problema.}{However this solution has one problem.}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.55,0:08:55.13,HnF,,0,0,0,,Si tiene un problema, no será tan buena.{So there’s a problem. It’s not good if there’s a problem.}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.13,0:08:56.80,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿Y qué problema es?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.15,0:09:00.82,HnF,,0,0,0,,Que decepcionaremos a Tsukihi.{The end result is that we’re going to deceive Tsukihi-chan.}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.71,0:09:07.55,HnF,,0,0,0,,Araragi, ¿habría algún problema si le mentimos a tu hermana?{¿estás en contra de mentir a tu hermana de cualquier forma?}{Araragi-senpai, are you opposed to lying to your sisters in any way?}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.48,0:09:10.82,HnF,,0,0,0,,No pasaría nada.{Ni lo más mínimo.}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.28,0:09:15.03,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,Y ahora el epílogo, o mejor, la conclusión.{And now for the epilogue, or rather, the punch line.}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.64,0:09:20.66,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,¿Por qué las compañeras de Tsukihi siguen pensando que existe una octava persona?{Why did Tsukihi’s fellow club members continue to obstinately believe in the ‘eighth person’?}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.17,0:09:24.00,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,Incluso después ver las soluciones y sus razones.{de haber sido guiados a la solución, después de haber sido guiados a la verdad.}{Even after being pointed to the correct answer, even after being pointed to reason,}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.00,0:09:26.04,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,¿Qué motivos tendrán para seguir creyendo?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.57,0:09:28.40,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,En resumen, si aporto esos {\i1}motivos{\i0},
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.40,0:09:33.01,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,si consigo explicarlo correctamente, Tsukihi tendrá que aceptarlo.{If I could provide a logical explanation for their irrationality, then Tsukihi might accept it.}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.66,0:09:36.05,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,Y Kanbaru los tiene.{Pero Kanbaru ya creo esa explicación.}{So Kanbaru added a reason for it.}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.63,0:09:42.43,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,Dijo que todos creían en la octava persona por el bien de Tsukihi.{The logic she came up with was that everyone was believing in the 'eighth person’ for Tsukihi’s sake.}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.43,0:09:47.90,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,Muchas veces, Tsukihi se llevaba té y dulces de la sala del club.{Tsukihi often takes as she pleases from the clubroom’s inventory of tea and snacks.}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.29,0:09:51.55,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,Aunque realmente no es algo por lo que armar un escándalo,{Well, it wasn’t something to make a big fuss over,}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.55,0:09:55.40,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,pero tampoco es algo muy elogiable.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.40,0:10:00.20,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,Si alguien lo mencionaba, podrían ser suspendidas las actividades del club.{podría ser suspendida de las actividades del club.}{if word got out, then it would certainly be possible that club activities would be suspended.}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.60,0:10:05.96,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,Y así, la "octava persona" aparece para encajar los números.{So, by hypothesizing an 'eighth person,’ the rate at which the inventory decreased was accounted for.}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.96,0:10:10.63,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,Sin la intención de crear una conspiración, y con el objetivo de proteger a Tsukihi,{Though they never planned to conspire against her, in order to protect Tsukihi,}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.63,0:10:14.68,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,todos aceptaron que una octava persona se había unido al club.{everyone acknowledged this 'eighth member’ to have joined the club.}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.68,0:10:17.71,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿Así que era eso? ¡Lo hacían por mí!{Is that so! Everyone did it for my sake!}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.71,0:10:19.73,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,Los idiotas son fáciles de engañar.{That idiot fell for it immediately.}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.73,0:10:24.18,HnF,,0,0,0,,Y pensar que intenté hacerlos entrar en razón tan testarudamente...{And here I was, boorishly saying that there was no such thing as ghosts,}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.18,0:10:27.13,HnF,,0,0,0,,¡Y resulta que era yo con mis acciones!{¡Y resulta que son mis acciones lo que era el fantasma!}{que era el vecino que elige los fantasmas}{but it was actually my attitude that was the ghost, huh!}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.13,0:10:28.64,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,Eso no ha sido muy inteligente.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.64,0:10:31.06,HnF,,0,0,0,,De acuerdo, me dejaré engañar.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.06,0:10:32.52,HnF,,0,0,0,,Yo misma me engañaré.{I’ll let myself fall for it.}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.52,0:10:34.22,HnF,,0,0,0,avoid,¡Y ese té me lo beberé!{I’ll let the tea be muddied.}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.81,0:10:36.88,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,Y cuando se lo conté a Kanbaru.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.72,0:10:41.20,HnF,,0,0,0,,Me pregunto si se dejó engañar por el club,{The tea ceremony club members or Araragi-senpai,}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.20,0:10:45.02,HnF,,0,0,0,,o si fue más por ti.
